parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic door locks can trap occupants inside the vehicle, posing a safety risk in emergency situations.
symptoms: The doors lock or unlock randomly
the doors cannot be manually unlocked
the doors freeze in a locked or unlocked position
occupants are trapped inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lamp assembly can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and may lead to a failure to comply with safety regulations.
symptoms: One or more rear lights do not function
including the rear parking light
rear turn signal
and rear brake light
the lights are dim or not visible
the dashboard warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger airbag is turned off
the dashboard light indicates an airbag malfunction
the airbag does not deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to idle poorly, leading to decreased performance, and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or fail to start.
symptoms: The engine idles very hard
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
the ignition coil is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly repair or replace the airbag module can lead to airbag failure or unintended deployment, which can cause injuries or accidents.
symptoms: Airbag module not replaced despite recall notice
dealer refusal to fix defect
airbag failure to deploy in crash situation
unintended airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dealer negligence and miscommunication can lead to delayed or incomplete repairs, putting vehicle occupants at risk of injury or accident.
symptoms: Dealer fails to perform recall repairs
dealer provides misleading information
incomplete or inaccurate paperwork.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lighting harness can cause the brake lights, turn signals, and reverse lights to malfunction or fail, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: Rear brake lights
turn signals
or reverse lights are dim
flickering
or not functioning; warning indicators on the dashboard; burnt or melted wiring or connectors in the rear lamp assemblies; headlight flickering.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Retaining Strap Bracket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank retaining strap bracket can cause the fuel tank to shift or become dislodged, potentially leading to fuel leaks, fires, or accidents.
symptoms: The fuel tank strap is hanging down
scraping against the ground
or broken
causing a loud scraping noise while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leak in the fuel tank sending unit can cause fuel to leak onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel is leaking from the fuel tank sending unit
creating a stream of fuel when the tank is full
with visible signs of fuel dripping from the unit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to hesitate, lose power, or stall, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or loses power while driving
and may not restart after shutting off.
